JOHANNESBURG - Eskom said that its technicians were working to restore power to large parts of Soweto after a blackout allegedly caused by vandalism. It warned that the Jabavu substation had been damaged beyond repair and that it could take several more days to reconnect customers to the grid. Affected areas include Western Jabavu, Jabavu, Mofolo Central, Molapo and White City. Eskom described the situation as "one of the biggest incidents of vandalism it's ever encountered". #EskomGauteng #MediaStatementJabavu substation vandalism results in supply interruption in Soweto townships@News24 @Radio702 @SABCNews @NewzroomAfrika @eNCA @IOL @ewnupdates @SowetanLIVE @SowetoUrban @SowetoTVchannel pic.twitter.com/IGNcUBb0Yt  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.